  Source:
    Title: Young India
    Editor: M. K. Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 22 Dec 1920
---
The tendency of human nature is to hide dirt, we do not want to see or
touch dirty things; we want to put them out of sight. And so must it
be with our speech. I would suggest that we should avoid even thinking
thoughts we would hide from the world.
